Error: Error: "The Server Could Not Allocate Enough Memory For The Startup. Please Check Your Startup Parameters."

Solution: This error occurs when running the Minecraft server requires more memory than what is currently allocated. To fix this problem, follow these steps:

1. Open your server directory and locate the startup script file.
2. Edit the startup script file and add the following line of code:
   java -Xmx<amount of memory> -Xms<amount of memory> -jar minecraft_server.jar nog
